description:
HGT - Planetary High Velocity Mixer

Overview
HGT was founded on January 2017, and is a technology innovative firm specializing in the production of high velocity mixers.

HGT is currently using the torque produced by the rotation and revolution of the mixers to combine chemically and physically distinct materials, allowing this procedure to be applicable to all steps of production in which combining materials are necessary. 

Moreover, given that mixers are domestically and internationally used during the production of electrical material, bio-fuels, chemical products, medicine, cosmetics, and food, we have filed a patent application for the technology behind high velocity mixers, giving us potential to conduct business outside the domestic market, complementing our goal to become a leader in the word market following our motto "Design New Technology"

description:
Hello, I'm Andy. My goal is to create entertaining videos mostly, but not only, for people who love cars & crashes. 

All the videos you'll find in this channel are recorded & edited by me and my sidekick, George, who helps with parts of the editing.
This channel is our full-time job. We're devoting a minimum of 100 hours per week to bring you the best BeamNG drive videos.

How we work:

Creating these videos is a lot harder & time consuming than you might think but it is what makes us and, hopefully, you happy!
We are playing BeamNG.drive, a PC Game featuring the ultimate soft-body physics and realism. 

The process, step by step:

- Recording the clips with Action! (10-15 hours, sometimes 15+)
- Editing & synchronizing the clips with music & addition of captions / sound effects - Premiere Pro (5-10 hours)  
- Descriptions, Thumbnails etc.  (2 hours)

We‚Äôre uploading 4 Videos per week on Tuesday, Thursday, Saturday & Sunday. Stay up to date by Subscribing!
Thank you :)

description:
Welcome to Helicopter Lessons in 10 Minutes or Less!  

My goal with this channel is to teach helicopter pilot topics, one-by-one, in a format that's easy to grasp. I try to keep all of the topics in a format that can be used on any scratch paper or a whiteboard in a briefing room.  Viewers can use these drawings as a study tool, training aids, or for demonstration purposes to pass check-rides.  

My name is Jacob. I'm an Apache Instructor Pilot and I love flying and teaching. If there are any topics you'd like covered, mention your idea in a video comment and I'll see what I can do. If you enjoy the videos, make sure to subscribe and leave feedback. 

Safe flying!

description:
Hi all!!!

My name is Jim and I'm the creator of this channel. This is my full time job and my mission is to bring you the highest quality and of high standard editing BeamNG drive videos with unique, meaningful and fun content.

BeamNG drive is the most realistic driving game that mimics every component of a vehicle in real time resulting in lifelike behavior.

All my videos are created by myself using the following programs : GeForce Experience for recording, Adobe Premiere Pro for editing and synchronizing the initially raw footage and Photoshop for thumbnails.

My weekly process consists of:
- Recording my clips ( 30 - 40 hours )
- Editing my clips ( 18 - 24 hours ) That includes editing in image, music, captions and sound effects.
-Thumbnails, description etc. roughly 10 hours.

I upload 3 times a week every Tuesday, Friday and Sunday, at 5pm GMT

Join me and be part of this adventure. 

Subscribe and stay tuned!

description:
This is Juice WRLD's official channel.

Chicago-area hip-hop musician Juice WRLD delivers introspective lyrics atop melodic production, echoing Travis Scott and Post Malone. Born Jarad Higgins in 1998, the Calumet Park artist grew up playing piano, drums, and guitar, turning to rap freestyling in high school. Influenced by rock music and Chicago drill from Lil Durk and Chief Keef, Higgins began recording as Juice TheKidd, a moniker derived from his haircut, which resembled 2Pac's in the film Juice.

His early tracks were all posted online, leading up to 2017's Juice WRLD 999 EP. Produced by Nick Mira and Sidepce, the set included the singles "Lucid Dreams (Forget Me)" and "All Girls Are the Same". Both tracks would also land on his official debut full-length album, Goodbye & Good Riddance, which peaked at number 15 on the Billboard 200 upon release in May 2018.

description: The California High-Speed Rail Authority is responsible for planning, designing, building and operation of the first high-speed rail system in the nation. California high-speed rail will connect the mega-regions of the state, contribute to economic development and a cleaner environment, create jobs and preserve agricultural and protected lands. The system will run from San Francisco to the Los Angeles basin in under three hours at speeds capable of over 200 miles per hour. The system will eventually extend to Sacramento and San Diego, totaling 800 miles with up to 24 stations. In addition, the Authority is working with regional partners to implement a state-wide rail modernization plan that will invest billions of dollars in local and regional rail lines to meet the state's 21st century transportation needs.

description:
My channel is a collection of golf swing videos of professional golfers. Most of the videos have been taken with the Casio Exilim EX-FH25 or Sony RX10  IV / RX100 VI cameras (at either 240 or 250 frames-per-second). Normally the videos are taken at a shutter speed of around 1/2500  to give sharpness to the club and hands during the downswing. If better equipment is available I will try it out!

Most of the videos have been taken at European Tour events ‚Äì mostly UK events - though sometimes I venture out as far as Denmark, Turkey and most recently Australia. All the videos are taken during practice days or pro-ams and are never taken during the tournament days.

Enjoy the videos!

Michael Field

description:
Hello and welcome to my channel! 

I speak Swedish, Russian, Finnish, English and very little Japanese!
I am from Helsinki, the capital of Finland!

I was born in 1993 and I lived in Turku from 1995 until 2013. I have studied languages at the University of Helsinki, and I also work as a guide, and have a part-time job. One of my hobbies is documenting elevators in my home country, and internationally (every once in a while, I get to travel a little!). Interests also include rail-based public transportation, ferries, cruiseferries, airplanes, music, movies, culture, cuisine and languages. On my channel, you'll find videos of elevators, public transportation, flights, ferries and cruiseferries - from Finland and abroad, and I especially like older elevators with character and style as they can be very unique, so stay tuned!

I've been using YouTube since September 2008.

description:
My youtube channel is a collection of RC and FPV related videos but also family/fun stuff, camera/tech bits and anything else that interests me.

I've flown RC heli's and planes for over 30 years on and off, quadcopters since 2012 and FPV since 2013, and have been making videos since S-VHS/8mm days.

I make youtube videos for fun and aim to make short useful videos where I feel I can do something a bit different, so I try to avoid common reviews unless I can do something different. 

Everything I review is bought with my own money as a normal customer (I am not a fan of paid reviews or reviewers), so I can give my open and honest opinion.

I pretty much delete any abusive/trolling comments, but try to respond to serious questions, but please read video descriptions first as I try to put details in there where possible, also please don't ask me for links as I don't recommend any particular vendor, and links are outdated within a day or two, so just search for best price in your country.

description: Lil Wayne is an American hip hop recording artist from New Orleans, Louisiana. In 1991, at the age of nine, Lil Wayne joined Cash Money Records as the youngest member of the label, and half of the duo The B.G.'z, alongside fellow New Orleans-based rapper Lil' Doogie. In 1996, Lil Wayne formed the Southern hip hop group Hot Boys, with his Cash Money label-mates Juvenile, Young Turk and Lil' Doogie (who now goes by B.G.). Hot Boys debuted with Get It How U Live! that same year. Lil Wayne gained most of his success with the group's major selling album Guerrilla Warfare (1999). Along with being the flagship artist of Cash Money Records, Lil Wayne is also the chief executive officer (CEO) of his own imprint, Young Money Entertainment, which he founded in 2005.

We are scientists, working for scientists.
Our belief is that each and every Biologist, Researcher and Physician should be able to explore and interact instantly with living cells without damaging them.

We have developed a disruptive technology which, for the first time, allows users to explore the inside of a living cell in 3D without the need for any labeling or other invasive methods.
The 3D Cell Explorer is a high speed, high resolution and non-invasive tool that can look deep inside biological systems. This allows you to record stunning 3D images of entire cells in just seconds and with a higher resolution than any conventional microscope on the market.
With the 3D Cell Explorer, researchers, students and medical doctors can directly experience what happens inside the living cell ‚Äì in real time!

Boy.

When are you going to do a voice reveal?
At 1,000 subscribers but some of you probably heard my voice before.

How many flight minutes do you have in PTFS?
19.9k at the time of writing this. [4/4/2021]

Are you going to be a pilot in real life?
Maybe?

When did you start playing PTFS?
I first played PTFS in 2017 but didn't really play it as my main game.

description:
Hello and welcome to my channel.  In 2014 I was asked by my mom to help find something to help her sleep.  She was looking for one of those little boxes you put next to the bed to play nature sounds, and asked me to help.  From what I found, they were terrible.  I realized that I could do so much better for her.  I bought my first recorder and got to work, and she loved them.  

I started my channel in 2015 and it didn't take long to realize that I was going to need a lot more that just a recorder.  And so it began!  Several new computers, nicer recorders, new video camera, and a slew of microphones later, here we are.  You wouldn't believe how much is actually involved with making each video! Every video takes several hours to edit, and that doesn't include the time and travel to actually make the recordings. Totally worth it!

I feel lucky to have helped so many people over the years.  Every recording is unique and I hope to make that perfect video and sound that helps you too.

description:
Cycle World, America's largest motorcycle media brand, works hard to deliver the full experience of motorcycling not only through words but video.
 
Offering a visual experience of motorcycle reviews, performance tests and shows, Cycle World's moto-journalistic style helps keep enthusiasts up-to-date on all the motorcycle industry's news.
 
Launched in 1962, Cycle World was created to be a high-quality motorcycle magazine founded on strong journalistic standards. Cycle World magazine was a pioneer in participatory moto-journalism, in which Cycle World editors actively participated in races and events as competitors to write the stories for the magazine.
 
Cycle World still continues to lead its category with in-depth, objective road tests as well as motorcycle and gear reviews.

Demonracer2 is a Fire Photography Youtube channel based out of New Jersey. First FP channel in the United States to reach 100k subscribers and second in the world! Mark is the sole photographer/videographer for DR2 and specializes in emergency response videos and on scene footage from incidents such as fire scenes, motor vehicle accidents, medical helicopter landings and much more. My videos have been viewed and shared all across the world and used for training purposes by many emergency agencies. And I am grateful for the friends and relationships that were built off my videos and this channel 

Thank you for taking the time to view my channel and videos. As I truly do appreciate all your views and subscriptions. If you like what you see here be sure to follow me on Instagram @demonracer2_Erv and Facebook at www.facebook.com/demonracer2 to stay up to date on my self along with my channel!

description:
Hey everyone, thanks for taking the time to visit my YouTube Channel. I grew up on a farm in Ohio and went to school for Agricultural Mechanics. I have spent my entire life around farms and farm equipment. After school I was a technician at a Farm Equipment dealer close to my home. After several years at the dealer of setting up equipment and working on stuff I moved on to work for Gehl Company as a traveling field service rep. I did this for 14.5 years then went to work for Versatile Ag as a service rep for 13 years. I recently left Versatile and went to work for PFG America who is the Deutz Fahr Tractor distributor in the USA. I am a precision and product specialist for their 6 cylinder tractors. 

My career has me traveling all over this great country and with all the farming action I see I thought I should share it all on YouTube.

All content on my channel is filmed by me and is not to be copied. 

Farmhand Mike is Trademarked. 





Thanks,

Mike Less - Farmhand Mike
